---
// AudienceSection — 3 audience cards
---

<section class="audience">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Who It's For</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">Built for engineering teams<br/>shipping with AI assistance.</h2>

    <div class="audience-grid">
      <div class="audience-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0s">
        <div class="audience-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
            <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/>
            <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Engineering Teams</h3>
        <p>Keep requirements, design intent, and verification in the repo. Teams get one contract layer that survives pull requests, code review, and CI instead of drifting across tools.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s">
        <div class="audience-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/>
            <line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/>
            <line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/>
            <path d="M7 8l3 3-3 3" opacity="0.8"/>
            <line x1="13" y1="14" x2="17" y2="14" opacity="0.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>AI Coding Workflows</h3>
        <p>Give agents precise scope, linked criteria, and machine-readable status. They can load the contract, make a change, and run the same verification loop your team trusts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="audience-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.2s">
        <div class="audience-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M20 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H8a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="12" cy="7" r="4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Solo Maintainers</h3>
        <p>Start with one spec file and one verification loop. Supersigil scales up without changing the basic workflow: write an MDX contract, link evidence, and run <code>verify</code>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .audience {
    padding: 8rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .audience-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .audience-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, background 0.3s;
  }
  .audience-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }
  .audience-icon {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .audience-icon svg { display: inline-block; }
  .audience-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .audience-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
  .audience-card code {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    color: var(--gold);
    background: rgba(201, 165, 92, 0.08);
    padding: 0.15em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  /* Light theme overrides */
  :global([data-theme='light']) .audience-card code {
    background: rgba(138, 108, 47, 0.1);
  }
</style>
